l. 76. Mycono e celsa: Myconus is not really lofty, but ‘the Latin poets are apt to call all islands high’ (Wagner). The insignificant Gyarus has no claim either on account of its position or its size to be considered the support of Delos, but its unpleasant associations (it was a penal settiement) made it more familiar than the suitable Tenos or Syra to Roman ears.
